    {
      "id": "6ad6ffa6988fd53d9ca96373bfe343b33b887b38",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-06-22 22:22:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI'm concerned about the testing for this patch.  We don't want to be landing a test that is introducing intermittent failures.\n\nDo we know why the scrub-performance test actually failed?  I had a look at it but didn't see anything obvious.  Unfortunately, just resubmitting the patch to Jira Logger doesn't re-trigger the Test-Parameters tests, so it may be necessary to submit a follow-on patch with:\n\nTest-Parameters: testlist=scrub-performance,scrub-performance \\\n        scrub-performance,scrub-performance\n\nor similar, so that it is run multiple times.  It may also make sense to include some more progress output into the tests themselves, so that we can see where it is failing or timing out.\n\nMarking negative for now until this is understood and resolved.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a92858e95d9f26d4a56902e6f565c3cf255e2f90",
